  <!--
    Other element.properties keys used by BPMN diagrams (free-form,
    no enum restriction in this XSD because they are stored as the
    flexible PropertiesType key/value pairs):

      adHoc            : boolean   — subprocess/subprocess-expanded marker (BPMN 2 §13.5)
      isSystem         : boolean   — black-box pool only (schema 1.8). true = IT system
                                     (positioned below the main process pool and kept with
                                     task.taskType "user" / "service" per R07); false =
                                     external entity / person / organisation (positioned
                                     above the main pool, R06 Send/Receive task typing).
                                     Set explicitly by the AI Plan workflow; falls back
                                     to a label-keyword regex for legacy/manual pools.
      labelOffsetX     : decimal   — gateway/event/data external label X offset
      labelOffsetY     : decimal   — gateway/event/data external label Y offset
      labelWidth       : decimal   — gateway/event/data external label width
      multiplicity     : "single" | "collection"  — data object/store
      role             : "input" | "output" | "none" — data object I/O marker
      state            : string    — data object state badge
      link             : string    — data object/store free-text document URL
      filename         : string    — data object/store document filename
      sharepointLink   : object    — data object/store linked SharePoint/OneDrive file (schema 1.22).
                                     JSON-encoded { driveId, itemId, name, webUrl }; set via the
                                     editor "Link SharePoint file…" button, previewed in-app.
      linkedDiagramId  : string    — collapsed subprocess / submachine / collapsed process drill-down link

    Value-chain element properties (chevron = Process, chevron-collapsed = Collapsed Process,
    process-group = Value Chain container):
      fillColor        : string    — per-element fill colour (hex, from process colour theme or auto-tint)
      description      : string    — process description text (multi-line)
      showDescription  : boolean   — whether to display the description box below the process

    Process-context element properties:
      Processes (use-case) support P-XX-NN numbering (e.g. P-HR-01).
      Hourglass (auto-scheduler) connectors use open-directed arrow type.
      System and hourglass actors are positioned to the right of the process group.
      Teams and actors are positioned based on their connected process side.

    BPMN event properties (schema 1.6):
      Event Type dropdown converts between start-event, intermediate-event, end-event.
      Trigger (formerly "Event Type") sets the event trigger (message, timer, error, etc.).
      Auto-connect rules: never TO a start event, never FROM an end event.
      Expanded Subprocesses of type event or transaction excluded from auto-connect.
      Nested expanded subprocesses lighten in shade (25% per level toward white).

    BPMN sequence connector rules (schema 1.6):
      S1: No sequence TO a non-boundary start event (auto-converts to intermediate).
      S2: Sequence TO a boundary start event IS allowed (from outside the host subprocess).
      S3: No sequence FROM a non-boundary end event (auto-converts to intermediate).
      S4: No sequence TO or FROM an Event Expanded Subprocess.
      S5: No sequence TO anything inside an Event Expanded Subprocess (from outside).
      S6: No sequence FROM anything inside an Event Expanded Subprocess (to outside).
      S7: Internal connections within an Event Expanded Subprocess ARE allowed.
      S8: Edge-mounted End/Intermediate Events cannot connect INTO their host subprocess.
      R23: Task type auto-set on message connector: non-System pool → Send/Receive,
           System pool → User regardless of direction.
      Force-connect override: Shift+Ctrl+Click bypasses all validation rules.
      Target highlighting synced with validation: green highlights match actual connectable targets.

    BPMN palette order (schema 1.6):
      Start, Intermediate, End, Task, Subprocess, Expanded Sub, Gateway, Pool,
      Data Object, Data Store, Annotation, Group.
    Pool/Lane header widths: Pool 45px, Lane/Sublane 36px (50% wider than original).

    AI generation features (schema 1.6):
      All diagram types support AI-assisted generation via the AI Generate panel.
      Users can type a prompt, dictate via speech-to-text, or attach a document
      (PDF with native document understanding, or text files: .txt, .md, .csv, .rtf).
      Saved prompts are filtered by diagram type and support edit/update.
      AI Rules & Preferences (admin) control generation behaviour per diagram type.

    AI Plan (two-phase) workflow for BPMN (schema 1.8):
      BPMN diagrams use a two-phase flow. Phase 1 (POST /api/ai/bpmn/plan)
      sends the prompt + rules to Sonnet and returns a normalised JSON plan
      ({ elements: AiElement[], connections: AiConnection[] }) without running
      layout. Phase 2 (POST /api/ai/bpmn/apply-layout) takes a (possibly
      user-edited) plan, validates via Zod, and runs the deterministic layout
      engine. The plan is exposed in the Diagram Editor via four synchronised
      tabs (Pools/Lanes, Elements, Connectors, Raw JSON) — edits made on any
      tab propagate to the others. The plan JSON is persisted alongside the
      saved Prompt record (Prompt.planJson column) so reloading a prompt
      restores both the text and the last structural draft.

      Green vs red rule split: rules under BPMN groups whose heading matches
      /layout|positioning|placement|spacing|sizing|arrangement|connector routing/i
      are categorised as layout-engine-enforced (red); all others are
      AI-enforced (green). Currently both sets are sent to Sonnet; future
      work will send only green rules to Sonnet with layout-only rules
      applied locally.

      R31 (no sequence to/from Event Expanded Subprocess) is enforced in four
      places: AI system prompt, layout engine filter, manual ADD_CONNECTOR
      reducer, UI drop-target highlighting. The layout filter treats a
      connection with no explicit type as sequence (matches downstream default).
  -->


